<h1 align=center >Dharma Protection</h1>

<p class=Body1><span style='font-family:DFKai-SB;mso-fareast-font-family:SimSun;
color:black'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<h2 align=center style=" font-style:italic">1. The Spirit</h2>

<p align=center style='margin-top:.25in;margin-right:0in;
margin-bottom:.25in;margin-left:0in;text-align:center'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-size:13.0pt'>The work of a Dharma Protector is very
sacred.<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=Body1 style='margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l9 level1 lfo7'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>1.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]>
Dharma protection originates from the needs to support Master in
promoting the Truth, to protect and safeguard Quan Yin Method, and to maintain
a good practicing environment for fellow initiates.</p>

<p class=Body1 style='margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l9 level1 lfo7'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>2.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]>
For many years, Dharma Protectors' spirit of sacrifice and dedication
won great support from fellow initiates.</p>

<p class=Body1 style='margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l9 level1 lfo7'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>3.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]>
It is a great challenge to work as Dharma Protector. Hence, this &lt;Manual for Dharma
Protection&gt; provides lots of precious experiences from senior protectors as
a reference to juniors to familiarise their roles quickly and accomplish their
tasks successfully.</p>

<p class=Body1 style='margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l9 level1 lfo7'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>4.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]>
All reminders in this manual are only a general guide. <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><u>Any instruction from Master at any time can override all and is
always the highest priority that all Dharma Protectors need to follow at that
moment.</u></b></p>

<p class=Body1><span style='font-family:DFKai-SB;mso-fareast-font-family:SimSun;
color:black'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<div style='mso-element:para-border-div;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;
mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 1.0pt;
margin-left:14.2pt;margin-right:27.2pt'>

<p align=center style='text-align:center;border:none;
mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in;mso-padding-alt:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 1.0pt'><strong><span
style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:Broadway'>Since the greatest Master in
Universe is right here, the job of Dharma Protection therefore becomes sacred.<o:p></o:p></span></strong></p>

</div>

<b><i><span lang=EN-SG style='font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:
"Cambria","serif";mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-bidi-font-family:
"Times New Roman";mso-ansi-language:EN-SG;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;
mso-bidi-language:AR-SA'><br clear=all style='page-break-before:always'>
</span></i></b>

<h2 align=center style=" font-style:italic">2. The Concept</h2>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='margin-top:.25in;margin-right:0in;
margin-bottom:.25in;margin-left:0in;text-align:center'><b><span
style='font-size:13.0pt'>One paves the road for his/her own practice when
performing Dharma Protection.<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=Body1 style='margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l9 level1 lfo7'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>1.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]>Master
said: "The more we serve others, the more merits we will have for our practice."</p>

<p class=Body1 style='margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l9 level1 lfo7'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>2.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]>Master
said: "We enlighten very fast when doing work. Focus on any work and it helps
to open our wisdom up. It also moves away stones on the path virtually, so as
to speed up the practice."</p>

<p class=Body1 style='margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l9 level1 lfo7'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>3.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]>Due
to Master's Grace and our great merits, we become Dharma Protectors. Being a
long term Dharma Protector, one should cherish the blessings very much.</p>

<p class=Body1 style='margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l9 level1 lfo7'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>4.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]>To
be a Dharma Protector, one needs to first put down ego, learn to be obedient
and subject one's self to order without questioning "Why?" and believing all is
the best arrangement by Master. Besides the respect to superiors, also to respect
the lessons from Master to fellow initiates and accept initiates' wisdom when
going through the tests.</p>

<p class=Body1 style='margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l9 level1 lfo7'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>5.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]>Working
members have no privilege over others, especially the Dharma Protectors. Dharma
Protectors should observe all regulations even more strictly without
compromise. Otherwise, one is not qualified.</p>

<p class=Body1 style='margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l9 level1 lfo7'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>6.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]>A
Dharma Protector should be honest, and should not use the position and work to
make personal gain.&nbsp;</p>

<p class=Body1 style='margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l9 level1 lfo7'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>7.<span 
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]>When
on duty, a Dharma Protector should regard the responsibility of Dharma Protection
as top priority, put down everything personal and devote one's self completely.</p>

<p class=Body1><span style='font-family:DFKai-SB;mso-fareast-font-family:SimSun;
color:black'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<div style='mso-element:para-border-div;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;
mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 1.0pt;
margin-left:14.2pt;margin-right:27.2pt'>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center;border:none;
mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in;mso-padding-alt:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 1.0pt'><strong><span
style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:Broadway'>Master said: "Picking up one
stone here equals to saving the need to encounter many stones outside."</span></strong></p>

</div>

<b><i><span lang=EN-SG style='font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:
"Cambria","serif";mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-bidi-font-family:
"Times New Roman";mso-ansi-language:EN-SG;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;
mso-bidi-language:AR-SA'><br clear=all style='page-break-before:always'>
</span></i></b>

<h2 align=center style=" font-style:italic">3. Rules for Working</h2>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='margin-top:.25in;margin-right:0in;
margin-bottom:.25in;margin-left:0in;text-align:center'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-size:13.0pt'>Focus on wisdom eye at all times and
recite five holy names silently.<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=Body1 style='margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l16 level1 lfo3'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>1.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]>Dharma
Protectors mainly maintain quietness and keep the centre's pure atmosphere. Pray
for Master's blessing in meditation before or a day before one's duty.</p>

<p class=Body1 style='margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l16 level1 lfo3'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>2.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]>Often
read Master's teachings to cultivate oneself with right concept of practice.</p>

<p class=Body1 style='margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l16 level1 lfo3'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>3.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]>Meditate
more than 3 hours daily. Complete daily meditation as much as possible before
duty, so as to get work done more perfectly.</p>

<p class=Body1 style='margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l16 level1 lfo3'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>4.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]>Dharma
Protectors should attend more Group Meditation. </p>

<p class=Body1 style='margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l16 level1 lfo3'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>5.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]>Dharma
Protectors on duty should keep a firm standpoint with polite attitude and mild
tone, in service mentality to create a good atmosphere to complete the duty. But
be cautious and dignified when strict enforcement is necessary.</p>

<p class=Body1 style='margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l16 level1 lfo3'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>6.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]>Be
solemn, especially when facing the public. Maintain silence at all times and
avoid chatting with other Dharma Protectors or fellow initiates.</p>

<p class=Body1 style='margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l16 level1 lfo3'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>7.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]>When
male and female Dharma Protectors support and help each other, works should be
clearly distributed and be carried out with dignified conduct.</p>

<p class=Body1 style='margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l16 level1 lfo3'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>8.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]>Dharma
Protectors should recognize the situations and must handle events timely and
strictly, in order to protect fellow initiates from incurring more karma.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-size:14.0pt;color:black'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<div style='mso-element:para-border-div;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;
mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 1.0pt;
margin-left:14.2pt;margin-right:27.2pt'>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center;border:none;
mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in;mso-padding-alt:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 1.0pt'><strong><span
style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:Broadway'>Master said: "To do Master's
work, one should at least meditate more than one hour on Quan Yin (sound
meditation).'"<o:p></o:p></span></strong></p>

</div>

<b><i><span lang=EN-SG style='font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:
