<h2 align=center style=" font-style:italic">4. Rules for Command</h2>


<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='margin-top:.25in;margin-right:0in;
margin-bottom:.25in;margin-left:0in;text-align:center'><b><span
style='font-size:13.0pt'>To become a Dharma Protector, one has to put down
one's ego beforehand.<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=Body1 style='margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l28 level1 lfo4'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>1.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]>Dharma
Protectors emphasize most the team spirit. Top priority is to execute and
complete commands. One should gently enquire on another suitable occasion for
any query to the command or service.</p>

<p class=Body1 style='margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l28 level1 lfo4'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>2.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]>Dharma
Protectors should always take initiative to spot, report and solve problem. For
situations that need immediate action, act immediately and remember to report the
details afterwards. </p>

<p class=Body1 style='margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l28 level1 lfo4'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>3.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]>Be
consistent in executing command, without adding self's ideas. Any compromise
will cause confusions like: "The last time it was allowed, why not this time?"</p>

<p class=Body1 style='margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l28 level1 lfo4'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>4.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]>When
dealing with fellow initiates, one should take full responsibility of dharma
protection and should not have any feelings of hesitation. We must be aware
that once our over-politeness or weak personalities lead to any error, it will
affect the public, not only a few initiates.</p>

<p class=Body1 style='margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l28 level1 lfo4'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>5.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]>When
executing instructions, sometimes we encounter fellow initiates' strong
reactions. Dharma Protectors should learn how to turn around the atmosphere and
solve it with perfect harmonized wisdom. It is better for fellow initiates to
complain at the Dharma Protectors rather than complain at the Centre.</p>

<p class=Body1 style='margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l28 level1 lfo4'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>6.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]>Dharma
Protectors should not ask "Why?" upon receiving instructions, but know clearly the
purpose and how to complete the tasks.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-size:14.0pt'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

