<h2 align=center style=" font-style:italic">5. Rules for Duty</h2>


<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='margin-top:.25in;margin-right:0in;
margin-bottom:.25in;margin-left:0in;text-align:center'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-size:13.0pt'>Being a Dharma Protector, one should be
honest and humble.<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=Body1 style='margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo5'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>1.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]>Strictly
execute the instructions, with care and a smile. One should be fair, whether it
is close friends or strangers.</p>

<p class=Body1 style='margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo5'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>2.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]>Understand
the current duties and methods clearly. For anything that is not clear, seek
superior's clarification first and do not make any decision without proper
authorization.</p>

<p class=Body1 style='margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo5'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>3.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]>Do
not leave the post when on duty, unless another Dharma Protector has arrived to
replace, or after receiving a withdrawal notice for your post.</p>

<p class=Body1 style='margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo5'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>4.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]><span
style='mso-bidi-font-family:"Courier New";color:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt'>Learn
to fulfill tasks in a tactful manner. Many tasks do not necessarily need to be
completed with words. Try to make use of body language, to achieve the same
effect.</span></p>

<p class=Body1 style='margin-left:.5in'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>

